[[File:Antoniobanfi01.jpg|thumb|Antonio Banfi]]
'''Antonio Banfi''' (Vimercate, 30 September 1886 – Milano, 22 July 1957) was an Italian philosopher and [[Italian senate|senator]].

Although influenced by the [[Marburg]] [[Neo-Kantianism|Neo-Kantians]] and [[Edmund Husserl]], whom he knew personally, Banfi moved away from Idealism and instead focused on [[Marxism]], in particular, [[historical materialism]].

Banfi joined the [[Italian Communist Party]] in 1947. He was elected to the Italian senate in 1948 and again in 1953.

