'''Christopher Donald Cordner''' (born December 30, 1949) is an [[Australia]]n philosopher and Associate Professor of [[Philosophy]] at the [[University of Melbourne]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Christopher Cordner |url=https://www.wheelercentre.com/people/christopher-cordner |website=[[The Wheeler Centre]] |accessdate=27 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Christopher Cordner |url=https://centreforethics.upce.cz/en/prof-christopher-cordner |website=Centre for ethics |accessdate=27 October 2018 |language=en}}</ref> He is known for his expertise on [[ethics]].<ref>{{cite journal |title=Book Reviews |journal=[[The Philosophical Quarterly]] |date=October 2003 |volume=53 |issue=213 |pages=605–632 |doi=10.1111/1467-9213.00337 |url=https://academic.oup.com/pq/article-abstract/53/213/605/1603192 |accessdate=27 October 2018 |language=en |issn=0031-8094}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Curthoys |first1=Jean |title=Understanding Others. "Ethical Encounter: The Depth of Moral Meaning", by Christopher Cordner. [review] |journal=[[Australian Book Review]] |date=September 2002 |url=https://dspace.flinders.edu.au/xmlui/handle/2328/1626 |accessdate=27 October 2018 |language=en |issn=0155-2864}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Westlund |first1=Andrea C. |title=Review of (Book 1) Narrative Identity and Moral Identity: A Practical Perspective; (Book 2) Practical Identity and Narrative Agency |journal=[[Notre Dame Philosophical Reviews]] |date=2 April 2009 |url=https://ndpr.nd.edu/news/book-1-narrative-identity-and-moral-identity-a-practical-perspective-book-2-practical-identity-and-narrative-agency/ |accessdate=27 October 2018 |issn=1538-1617}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Gleeson |first1=Andrew |title='Philosophy, Ethics, and a Common Humanity: Essays in Honour of Raimond Gaita', edited by Christopher Cordner |journal=[[Australasian Journal of Philosophy]] |date=30 August 2012 |volume=91 |issue=1 |pages=193–196 |doi=10.1080/00048402.2012.717955 |url=https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/00048402.2012.717955 |accessdate=27 October 2018 |language=en |issn=0004-8402}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Lemmens |first1=Willem |title=Book Review: Philosophy, Ethics and a Common Humanity: Essays in Honour of Raimond Gaita, edited by Christopher Cordner |journal=[[Journal of Moral Philosophy]] |date=22 March 2014 |volume=11 |issue=2 |pages=233–236 |doi=10.1163/17455243-01102001 |url=http://booksandjournals.brillonline.com/content/journals/10.1163/17455243-01102001 |accessdate=27 October 2018 |language=en |issn=1745-5243}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Fetterolf |first1=Elianna |title=Philosophy, Ethics and A Common Humanity: Essays in Honour of Raimond Gaita Edited by Christopher Cordner Routledge, 2011, £65, pp. xv + 233 |journal=Philosophy |date=July 2012 |volume=87 |issue=3 |pages=456–461 |doi=10.1017/S0031819112000228 |url=https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/philosophy/article/philosophy-ethics-and-a-common-humanity-essays-in-honour-of-raimond-gaita-edited-by-cordner-christopherroutledge-2011-65-pp-xv-233/C08E39E3615D82A2E510D5AE3B4C910E |accessdate=27 October 2018 |language=en |issn=1469-817X}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=McGhee |first1=Michael |title=ChristopherCordner (ed.), Philosophy, Ethics and a Common Humanity: Essays in Honour of Raimond Gaita (London: Routledge, 2011). xv + 239, price £65.00 hb. |journal=Philosophical Investigations |date=2 June 2014 |volume=37 |issue=3 |pages=281–285 |doi=10.1111/phin.12056 |url=https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1111/phin.12056 |accessdate=27 October 2018 |language=en |issn=0190-0536}}</ref> Cordner is a recipient of [[Rhodes Scholarship]] (1972).<ref>{{cite web |title=THEORY AND ANTI-THEORY IN ETHICS |url=http://www.flinders.edu.au/ehl/fms/hums_research/firthfocus/Philosophy%20Workshop.pdf |accessdate=27 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Rhodes Scholars at the University of Melbourne |url=https://about.unimelb.edu.au/notable-alumni-staff/rhodes-scholars |website=Un